## Agent skills

### Project brain

Read `BUSINESS_LOGIC.md` first for product fundamentals, core domain concepts,
non-negotiable rules, and decision references. Future task plans must cite the
relevant `BUSINESS_LOGIC.md` section before implementation.

`CONTEXT.md` remains a generated historical mirror from the Obsidian vault. Use
`docs/context/INDEX.md` to locate narrow sections when old context is needed;
do not read the whole file by default.

### Issue tracker

{{issueTrackerDescription}}

### Work history

Shipped work is summarized in `.history/DD.MM.YYYY/README.md`. Use separated
dated worklog files only; do not use issue comments as the project memory.
After every successful coding session, follow `docs/agents/session-close.md`.

### Domain docs

Use `BUSINESS_LOGIC.md`, `docs/`, and `docs/adr/` as tracked source material.
See `docs/agents/domain.md`.

### Coding principles

Follow `docs/CODING_PRINCIPLES.md`: simple direct code, YAGNI, KISS, pragmatic
DRY, existing conventions, explicit boundaries, fail-fast validation, and
focused tests.

### Agent memory

Use repo automation from `scripts/`:

- `scripts/memory_index.py` indexes project Markdown.
- `scripts/memory_search.py` searches indexed Markdown.
- `scripts/memory_bundle.py` writes a focused Markdown bundle for a task.
- `scripts/sync-context.sh` syncs the generated historical `CONTEXT.md`.

Generated memory files live under `.memory/` and are gitignored.
